In 2005 when CCP was developing the game, they realized they'd need to split the galaxy in various regions at the time, base on player skill level. Back then it was all an Microsoft Access database of systems. There was the system name, then that linked to a region name, which had a security status. However the development team who was working on the system list player conquerable space forgot to write in the values for the in game security status, and upon printing the table in sql to confirm the names, that field was "NULL" and it overflowed the SSH buffer terminating the connection and requiring an iDRAC login.    The name "Nullsec" stuck as an internal joke, and then players picked up on it after 0.0, 0.1 etc never took off past 2009
